  "target_response": {
    "text": "Don't treat the 650 as a precise bill to repay — wrist-based calorie burn is an estimate, and single-ride numbers can be off by a wide margin in either direction. For holding weight steady, the better system is to eat to consistent habits and steer by outcomes: your morning weight trend and hunger across two to three weeks tell you whether you're in balance far more reliably than any single day's estimated burn. Practically, after a ride like today's 62-minute effort, eat a normal meal with carbs and protein and let appetite do the fine-tuning; save deliberate extra fuelling for genuinely long sessions. Then adjust by trend: if your weight drifts down and training feels flat, add a bit; if it drifts up, trim a bit. The watch number is a rough guide, never a target.",
